<p>
<span id="SENTENCE_282">It was at this time, his friend Hannay tells us, that he first had the pleasure of seeing him.</span>
<span id="SENTENCE_283">'"Vanity Fair,"' he adds, 'was then unfinished, but its success was made; and he spoke frankly and genially of his work and his career.</span>
<span id="SENTENCE_284">"Vanity Fair" always, we think, ranked in his own mind as best in story of his greater books; and he once pointed out to us the very house in Russell</span>
